WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.497 align:middle line:90%


00:00:01.497 --> 00:00:04.990 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:04.990 --> 00:00:28.490 align:middle line:90%


00:00:28.490 --> 00:00:31.850 align:middle line:10%
>> What is really going on when
some meaningful coincidence

00:00:31.850 --> 00:00:33.780 align:middle line:10%
occurs in your own life?

00:00:33.780 --> 00:00:36.950 align:middle line:10%
How do you recognize the
message of synchronicity?

00:00:36.950 --> 00:00:39.110 align:middle line:84%
My guest today will
show you how to watch

00:00:39.110 --> 00:00:41.780 align:middle line:84%
for the little hints in
life that are guiding you

00:00:41.780 --> 00:00:43.070 align:middle line:90%
to your next step.

00:00:43.070 --> 00:00:45.650 align:middle line:84%
He's the author of
"Synchronicity as Spiritual

00:00:45.650 --> 00:00:49.330 align:middle line:84%
Guidance" and 16 other
books on spirituality,

00:00:49.330 --> 00:00:51.770 align:middle line:84%
and an honored guest
at the Wisdom Network.

00:00:51.770 --> 00:00:53.570 align:middle line:90%
Welcome, Dr. Mark Thurston.

00:00:53.570 --> 00:00:54.723 align:middle line:90%
Thanks for being with us.

00:00:54.723 --> 00:00:55.640 align:middle line:90%
>> Thank you, Carolyn.

00:00:55.640 --> 00:00:56.660 align:middle line:90%
Good to be here.

00:00:56.660 --> 00:00:59.330 align:middle line:84%
>> So there are a lot of
synchronistic events happening

00:00:59.330 --> 00:01:02.160 align:middle line:84%
all the time, and you say there
are ways that we can recognize

00:01:02.160 --> 00:01:02.960 align:middle line:90%
those.

00:01:02.960 --> 00:01:05.450 align:middle line:84%
There are hints that
are being given.

00:01:05.450 --> 00:01:08.780 align:middle line:84%
What are some of those hints
that we can pay attention to

00:01:08.780 --> 00:01:09.803 align:middle line:90%
in our own life?

00:01:09.803 --> 00:01:12.470 align:middle line:10%
>> Well, some of their hints are
things that happen in our inner

00:01:12.470 --> 00:01:14.640 align:middle line:10%
life, our dreams,
our intuitions,

00:01:14.640 --> 00:01:16.940 align:middle line:10%
our meditation experiences.

00:01:16.940 --> 00:01:18.440 align:middle line:10%
But just as surely,
there are things

00:01:18.440 --> 00:01:22.070 align:middle line:10%
that happen in our outer life,
little coincidences, things

00:01:22.070 --> 00:01:24.480 align:middle line:10%
that happen that by themselves,
would just be random,

00:01:24.480 --> 00:01:26.810 align:middle line:10%
but because they touch
us in a certain way,

00:01:26.810 --> 00:01:31.100 align:middle line:10%
it's suggested that it may be
guidance that's flowing to us.

00:01:31.100 --> 00:01:33.050 align:middle line:84%
>> I think the word
synchronistic came from--

00:01:33.050 --> 00:01:34.022 align:middle line:90%
was it Freud?

00:01:34.022 --> 00:01:35.480 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, Carl Jung
coined the term.

00:01:35.480 --> 00:01:36.680 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah, that's right.

00:01:36.680 --> 00:01:38.360 align:middle line:84%
>> And he recognized,
as we all do,

00:01:38.360 --> 00:01:41.780 align:middle line:84%
that cause and effect is a
spiritual law and a physical

00:01:41.780 --> 00:01:43.850 align:middle line:90%
law that shapes our experience.

00:01:43.850 --> 00:01:46.580 align:middle line:84%
But he suggested there was
also a complementary law,

00:01:46.580 --> 00:01:49.940 align:middle line:84%
the other side of the coin,
and that life is connected,

00:01:49.940 --> 00:01:52.340 align:middle line:84%
that there are meaningful
coincidences where things don't

00:01:52.340 --> 00:01:55.040 align:middle line:84%
really cause each other,
and yet, we experience them

00:01:55.040 --> 00:01:57.170 align:middle line:90%
as being linked in some way.

00:01:57.170 --> 00:02:00.530 align:middle line:84%
>> It seems like this is
something that as we move from

00:02:00.530 --> 00:02:05.690 align:middle line:84%
maybe a life of
numbness or on the path,

00:02:05.690 --> 00:02:07.920 align:middle line:84%
trying to keep up with
day to day activities,

00:02:07.920 --> 00:02:11.090 align:middle line:84%
if we back up and really
see that there's some order

00:02:11.090 --> 00:02:13.530 align:middle line:90%
in things in our life.

00:02:13.530 --> 00:02:15.890 align:middle line:84%
>> And I like to think that
noticing synchronicity is

00:02:15.890 --> 00:02:18.920 align:middle line:84%
a matter of developing another
kind of attention that we

00:02:18.920 --> 00:02:20.690 align:middle line:90%
typically have in life.

00:02:20.690 --> 00:02:21.800 align:middle line:90%
Our lives get so busy.

00:02:21.800 --> 00:02:23.640 align:middle line:84%
We rush from one
thing to the next.

00:02:23.640 --> 00:02:27.170 align:middle line:84%
And we often don't stop and
pause to listen inwardly

00:02:27.170 --> 00:02:30.020 align:middle line:84%
or to really watch outwardly
for these synchronistic events.

00:02:30.020 --> 00:02:30.980 align:middle line:90%
>> Give us an idea.

00:02:30.980 --> 00:02:34.880 align:middle line:84%
Like, in your own life,
say, today or a typical day,

00:02:34.880 --> 00:02:37.850 align:middle line:84%
where you might be paying
attention when maybe 20 years

00:02:37.850 --> 00:02:39.620 align:middle line:90%
ago you weren't.

00:02:39.620 --> 00:02:41.960 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, let me tell you
one story of a synchronistic

00:02:41.960 --> 00:02:43.835 align:middle line:90%
experience that I had.

00:02:43.835 --> 00:02:45.770 align:middle line:84%
I had hoped to make
a trip to Europe

00:02:45.770 --> 00:02:48.560 align:middle line:84%
to put on some workshops,
but I knew in order

00:02:48.560 --> 00:02:50.510 align:middle line:84%
to pull that off I
would need a sponsor.

00:02:50.510 --> 00:02:52.475 align:middle line:84%
I especially wanted
to go to Germany,

00:02:52.475 --> 00:02:54.950 align:middle line:84%
and I didn't really know who
could do that for me-- help me

00:02:54.950 --> 00:02:56.090 align:middle line:90%
with that.

00:02:56.090 --> 00:02:59.480 align:middle line:84%
And I was driving home from work
thinking about this problem,

00:02:59.480 --> 00:03:01.820 align:middle line:84%
and as I was sitting
at a red light,

00:03:01.820 --> 00:03:05.090 align:middle line:84%
I happened to notice the license
plate of the person right

00:03:05.090 --> 00:03:06.440 align:middle line:90%
in front of me.

00:03:06.440 --> 00:03:07.870 align:middle line:84%
It was a so-called
vanity license

00:03:07.870 --> 00:03:10.370 align:middle line:84%
plate, where the person pays a
little extra money every year

00:03:10.370 --> 00:03:13.240 align:middle line:84%
and they can have their
license say whatever they want.

00:03:13.240 --> 00:03:15.305 align:middle line:84%
And that license plate
in front of me said Rose,

00:03:15.305 --> 00:03:21.760 align:middle line:84%
R-O-S-E space M. And I suddenly
remembered that I knew someone,

00:03:21.760 --> 00:03:25.270 align:middle line:84%
a friend in Germany, whose
name was Rose Morath,

00:03:25.270 --> 00:03:27.800 align:middle line:84%
and it occurred to me she might
be the very person who could

00:03:27.800 --> 00:03:30.372 align:middle line:84%
help me put this series
of workshops together.

00:03:30.372 --> 00:03:32.330 align:middle line:84%
And in fact, about a year
later, they happened,

00:03:32.330 --> 00:03:34.105 align:middle line:90%
and she was the sponsor.

00:03:34.105 --> 00:03:35.480 align:middle line:84%
Now, I think Jung
would call that

00:03:35.480 --> 00:03:37.610 align:middle line:90%
a synchronistic occurrence.

00:03:37.610 --> 00:03:39.980 align:middle line:84%
It wasn't caused-- it
wasn't as if the person who

00:03:39.980 --> 00:03:43.700 align:middle line:84%
had that license plate thought
several months earlier,

00:03:43.700 --> 00:03:46.400 align:middle line:84%
there's somebody in Germany
named Rose Morath, and surely

00:03:46.400 --> 00:03:47.960 align:middle line:84%
several months from
now, a guy named

00:03:47.960 --> 00:03:49.550 align:middle line:84%
Mark Thurston's
going to be sitting

00:03:49.550 --> 00:03:51.350 align:middle line:84%
behind me at a red
light, and he's

00:03:51.350 --> 00:03:53.010 align:middle line:84%
going to need to
think of her name.

00:03:53.010 --> 00:03:55.850 align:middle line:84%
That's crazy to imagine
that cause and effect would

00:03:55.850 --> 00:03:57.260 align:middle line:90%
have caused this.

00:03:57.260 --> 00:04:02.790 align:middle line:84%
>> But how are we more receptive
to these things happening?

00:04:02.790 --> 00:04:05.280 align:middle line:90%
You paid attention to that.

00:04:05.280 --> 00:04:08.690 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, I think it's a
matter of developing a certain

00:04:08.690 --> 00:04:10.700 align:middle line:84%
alertness-- inner
and outer alertness.

00:04:10.700 --> 00:04:12.200 align:middle line:84%
I know in my own
life that trying

00:04:12.200 --> 00:04:16.130 align:middle line:84%
to keep a regular meditation
time, at least daily,

00:04:16.130 --> 00:04:19.700 align:middle line:84%
is important for developing
that kind of sensitivity.

00:04:19.700 --> 00:04:21.740 align:middle line:84%
I think watching my
dreams, and sometimes I

00:04:21.740 --> 00:04:24.200 align:middle line:84%
think synchronistic things
can come to us via dreams,

00:04:24.200 --> 00:04:27.500 align:middle line:84%
but just being attentive to
one's soul life through dreams

00:04:27.500 --> 00:04:30.920 align:middle line:84%
can also attune us and
awaken us to that kind

00:04:30.920 --> 00:04:34.220 align:middle line:90%
of daytime alertness as well.

00:04:34.220 --> 00:04:37.047 align:middle line:84%
Just watching for it,
keeping a journal-- keeping

00:04:37.047 --> 00:04:39.380 align:middle line:84%
a spiritual journal of some
sort, what you're recording,

00:04:39.380 --> 00:04:41.297 align:middle line:84%
what's happening in your
inner and outer life,

00:04:41.297 --> 00:04:44.110 align:middle line:84%
all these are tools that
can make it more frequent.

00:04:44.110 --> 00:04:48.083 align:middle line:84%
>> And the journaling, too,
you're actually asking for--

00:04:48.083 --> 00:04:49.750 align:middle line:84%
journaling what's
going on in your life.

00:04:49.750 --> 00:04:52.430 align:middle line:84%
But perhaps you've got a
question that you are pondering

00:04:52.430 --> 00:04:54.440 align:middle line:90%
and you're asking for insight.

00:04:54.440 --> 00:04:56.840 align:middle line:84%
That's a time to be
more aware, isn't it?

00:04:56.840 --> 00:04:59.450 align:middle line:84%
>> And I advocate working in
a very intentional way with

00:04:59.450 --> 00:05:01.170 align:middle line:90%
getting guidance.

00:05:01.170 --> 00:05:01.970 align:middle line:90%
>> Like how?

00:05:01.970 --> 00:05:04.460 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, let me describe an
eight step sequence that I

00:05:04.460 --> 00:05:06.980 align:middle line:84%
encourage people to follow,
and it's part of my book,

00:05:06.980 --> 00:05:09.350 align:middle line:84%
"Synchronicity as
Spiritual Guidance."

00:05:09.350 --> 00:05:11.310 align:middle line:84%
The steps are pretty
straightforward.

00:05:11.310 --> 00:05:13.780 align:middle line:84%
The first is to have a
core value for your life,

00:05:13.780 --> 00:05:16.730 align:middle line:84%
or what Edgar Cayce, as
a spiritual philosopher

00:05:16.730 --> 00:05:18.680 align:middle line:84%
and spiritual
psychologist, called

00:05:18.680 --> 00:05:20.320 align:middle line:90%
setting a spiritual ideal.

00:05:20.320 --> 00:05:22.120 align:middle line:84%
But a core value,
what you're going

00:05:22.120 --> 00:05:25.070 align:middle line:84%
to put at the heart of your
life, that's the first step.

00:05:25.070 --> 00:05:28.022 align:middle line:84%
>> Is that something that
you automatically know?

00:05:28.022 --> 00:05:29.480 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, I think
you can intuit it,

00:05:29.480 --> 00:05:31.850 align:middle line:84%
but I think it often
involves some self-study--

00:05:31.850 --> 00:05:33.500 align:middle line:90%
some self-examination.

00:05:33.500 --> 00:05:35.540 align:middle line:84%
For one person, it's
peace, for someone else,

00:05:35.540 --> 00:05:37.940 align:middle line:84%
it's love, for someone
else, it's fairness,

00:05:37.940 --> 00:05:39.530 align:middle line:90%
for someone else, it's joy.

00:05:39.530 --> 00:05:42.380 align:middle line:84%
>> So before we go
to the second one,

00:05:42.380 --> 00:05:45.590 align:middle line:84%
how would we find out
what our core value is?

00:05:45.590 --> 00:05:48.540 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, I think it's a
matter of asking yourself,

00:05:48.540 --> 00:05:50.870 align:middle line:84%
what do I want to have
at the center of my life?

00:05:50.870 --> 00:05:53.725 align:middle line:84%
What is the spirit or what
is the value or the quality

00:05:53.725 --> 00:05:55.850 align:middle line:84%
that, more than anything
else, I would like to have

00:05:55.850 --> 00:05:57.470 align:middle line:90%
guiding and directing me?

00:05:57.470 --> 00:06:01.132 align:middle line:84%
>> Does it have to be
somewhat of a spiritual ideal,

00:06:01.132 --> 00:06:04.820 align:middle line:84%
a spiritual attribute,
if you will?

00:06:04.820 --> 00:06:07.250 align:middle line:84%
>> It could be something
as simple as fairness.

00:06:07.250 --> 00:06:10.100 align:middle line:84%
I think for many people,
a core value of fairness

00:06:10.100 --> 00:06:11.815 align:middle line:90%
is a good starting point.

00:06:11.815 --> 00:06:13.940 align:middle line:84%
And they're not ready to
say Christ, consciousness,

00:06:13.940 --> 00:06:14.730 align:middle line:90%
or Buddha.

00:06:14.730 --> 00:06:14.930 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:06:14.930 --> 00:06:16.490 align:middle line:10%
>> But simply being
fair for them--

00:06:16.490 --> 00:06:18.508 align:middle line:10%
>> Honest and harmless.

00:06:18.508 --> 00:06:19.800 align:middle line:90%
>> All those are possibilities.

00:06:19.800 --> 00:06:20.590 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:06:20.590 --> 00:06:21.965 align:middle line:84%
>> And in this
guidance sequence,

00:06:21.965 --> 00:06:24.350 align:middle line:84%
you've got to have that
as the starting point.

00:06:24.350 --> 00:06:26.965 align:middle line:84%
Because as potential guidance
comes into your mind,

00:06:26.965 --> 00:06:28.340 align:middle line:84%
comes into your
attention, you've

00:06:28.340 --> 00:06:30.980 align:middle line:84%
got to have some point of
reference to evaluate it.

00:06:30.980 --> 00:06:32.000 align:middle line:90%
>> Would it change?

00:06:32.000 --> 00:06:34.190 align:middle line:84%
Would you have a core
ideal today or value

00:06:34.190 --> 00:06:36.180 align:middle line:84%
today that in 10 years
would be something else?

00:06:36.180 --> 00:06:36.980 align:middle line:90%
>> Definitely.

00:06:36.980 --> 00:06:38.900 align:middle line:84%
I think we grow and
develop and we mature

00:06:38.900 --> 00:06:41.420 align:middle line:90%
spiritually, emotionally, sure.

00:06:41.420 --> 00:06:45.200 align:middle line:84%
>> I can see even having a
core ideal or value today,

00:06:45.200 --> 00:06:47.210 align:middle line:84%
and then tomorrow having
something else as well.

00:06:47.210 --> 00:06:49.850 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, I would hope one's
core value wouldn't change quite

00:06:49.850 --> 00:06:51.380 align:middle line:90%
that often.

00:06:51.380 --> 00:06:53.870 align:middle line:84%
I think it finds
ways of being applied

00:06:53.870 --> 00:06:54.960 align:middle line:90%
a little bit differently.

00:06:54.960 --> 00:06:57.860 align:middle line:84%
If my core value
was love, the way

00:06:57.860 --> 00:07:00.440 align:middle line:84%
I express it in my relationship
with my son or daughter

00:07:00.440 --> 00:07:02.815 align:middle line:84%
might be a little bit different
than the way I express it

00:07:02.815 --> 00:07:03.950 align:middle line:90%
at work with a colleague.

00:07:03.950 --> 00:07:04.790 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:07:04.790 --> 00:07:07.670 align:middle line:84%
>> So we can have ideals and
aspirations that are more

00:07:07.670 --> 00:07:09.160 align:middle line:90%
situational.

00:07:09.160 --> 00:07:14.000 align:middle line:84%
What I'm advocating is a core
for this spiritual ideal that's

00:07:14.000 --> 00:07:17.040 align:middle line:84%
going to be the starting point
for working with guidance.

00:07:17.040 --> 00:07:19.905 align:middle line:84%
Then a second step is
to formulate a question.

00:07:19.905 --> 00:07:21.530 align:middle line:84%
And you'd be surprised
how often people

00:07:21.530 --> 00:07:24.030 align:middle line:84%
don't want to get that
specific about their question.

00:07:24.030 --> 00:07:26.030 align:middle line:84%
They just want to say,
well, tell me what to do,

00:07:26.030 --> 00:07:28.190 align:middle line:84%
or what should I
do next in my life?

00:07:28.190 --> 00:07:30.452 align:middle line:84%
But as we make that
question much more specific,

00:07:30.452 --> 00:07:31.910 align:middle line:84%
and even write it
down in a journal

00:07:31.910 --> 00:07:34.430 align:middle line:84%
or on a piece of paper,
what is it you want to know?

00:07:34.430 --> 00:07:37.910 align:middle line:84%
And actually to write
it out, pen or pencil

00:07:37.910 --> 00:07:38.820 align:middle line:90%
on a piece of paper.

00:07:38.820 --> 00:07:42.640 align:middle line:84%
>> Why is it that we don't
want to write it out sometimes

00:07:42.640 --> 00:07:44.810 align:middle line:90%
and really ask the question?

00:07:44.810 --> 00:07:47.060 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, sometimes we
have to confront our fears

00:07:47.060 --> 00:07:49.340 align:middle line:84%
or our doubts or our
lack of self-esteem,

00:07:49.340 --> 00:07:51.500 align:middle line:84%
or there's probably a
myriad set of reasons.

00:07:51.500 --> 00:07:53.930 align:middle line:84%
>> That we might get what
we want, I would think--

00:07:53.930 --> 00:07:56.780 align:middle line:84%
>> Or that we don't deserve
what we're seeking for.

00:07:56.780 --> 00:08:00.290 align:middle line:84%
Lots of possibilities for why
we avoid that second step.

00:08:00.290 --> 00:08:03.020 align:middle line:84%
But let's suppose we
can get a core value,

00:08:03.020 --> 00:08:05.870 align:middle line:84%
we can really write out
exactly what our question is.

00:08:05.870 --> 00:08:08.330 align:middle line:84%
Then before we start looking
for spiritual guidance,

00:08:08.330 --> 00:08:10.220 align:middle line:84%
the next couple of
steps involve working

00:08:10.220 --> 00:08:12.590 align:middle line:84%
with our conscious,
rational minds.

00:08:12.590 --> 00:08:15.770 align:middle line:84%
So step three is to collect
all the information or pieces

00:08:15.770 --> 00:08:19.700 align:middle line:84%
of data we have access to in
the waking, logical, analytical

00:08:19.700 --> 00:08:20.860 align:middle line:90%
state.

00:08:20.860 --> 00:08:24.038 align:middle line:84%
>> I want to even go
back to the third step.

00:08:24.038 --> 00:08:25.330 align:middle line:10%
>> That's the one we're on now.

00:08:25.330 --> 00:08:25.580 align:middle line:10%
>> OK.

00:08:25.580 --> 00:08:26.830 align:middle line:10%
I guess the second step, then.

00:08:26.830 --> 00:08:29.870 align:middle line:84%
What would be a kind of
question that we might ask?

00:08:29.870 --> 00:08:33.603 align:middle line:84%
I think it might help
in following along.

00:08:33.603 --> 00:08:36.020 align:middle line:10%
What would be something-- if
our core value was love, then

00:08:36.020 --> 00:08:38.299 align:middle line:10%
what would be a question that
we might ask in the second step?

00:08:38.299 --> 00:08:40.129 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, maybe you have a
question about your career.

00:08:40.129 --> 00:08:41.030 align:middle line:90%
>> OK.

00:08:41.030 --> 00:08:42.860 align:middle line:84%
>> Should I continue
in my current job?

00:08:42.860 --> 00:08:44.510 align:middle line:84%
Or is it time to
retire from that

00:08:44.510 --> 00:08:46.340 align:middle line:90%
and start on a second career?

00:08:46.340 --> 00:08:48.020 align:middle line:90%
That's a very specific question.

00:08:48.020 --> 00:08:51.620 align:middle line:84%
In fact, that one can be
posed in a yes, no answer.

00:08:51.620 --> 00:08:54.230 align:middle line:84%
And many people find as they
work with spiritual guidance

00:08:54.230 --> 00:08:57.360 align:middle line:84%
in the fifth and sixth
step in this sequence

00:08:57.360 --> 00:08:59.810 align:middle line:84%
that if the question has
been worded in a yes, no way,

00:08:59.810 --> 00:09:03.540 align:middle line:84%
it's easier for them to discern
the guidance as it comes.

00:09:03.540 --> 00:09:05.540 align:middle line:84%
But I've often worked
with open ended questions,

00:09:05.540 --> 00:09:07.720 align:middle line:90%
and it can work that way, too.

00:09:07.720 --> 00:09:09.220 align:middle line:84%
So with step three,
we're just going

00:09:09.220 --> 00:09:11.720 align:middle line:84%
to use our common sense
and our conscious minds.

00:09:11.720 --> 00:09:16.070 align:middle line:84%
We collect information, get all
the pieces we can consciously.

00:09:16.070 --> 00:09:17.780 align:middle line:84%
And then for step
four, we arrive

00:09:17.780 --> 00:09:20.510 align:middle line:84%
at a tentative or
provisional decision.

00:09:20.510 --> 00:09:22.240 align:middle line:84%
We're not going
to act on it yet,

00:09:22.240 --> 00:09:25.760 align:middle line:84%
but we've said, from the
best I know so far, here's

00:09:25.760 --> 00:09:27.890 align:middle line:90%
what my decision would be.

00:09:27.890 --> 00:09:30.260 align:middle line:84%
>> What I'm hearing,
too, at this point,

00:09:30.260 --> 00:09:34.970 align:middle line:84%
you still have not focused on
any obstacles or any reasons

00:09:34.970 --> 00:09:37.820 align:middle line:84%
why I cannot have
what I want in life.

00:09:37.820 --> 00:09:40.280 align:middle line:84%
You're really
co-creating, if you will.

00:09:40.280 --> 00:09:42.770 align:middle line:84%
You're actually getting
in touch with what it is

00:09:42.770 --> 00:09:45.640 align:middle line:90%
that you actually want in life.

00:09:45.640 --> 00:09:48.560 align:middle line:84%
>> Now, some of the obstacles
may come up as you think about

00:09:48.560 --> 00:09:50.840 align:middle line:84%
what information you
have access to right now.

00:09:50.840 --> 00:09:53.180 align:middle line:84%
That third step,
you may recognize,

00:09:53.180 --> 00:09:56.845 align:middle line:84%
well, I can't really quit my job
because my paycheck is so good

00:09:56.845 --> 00:09:58.470 align:middle line:84%
and I have these
financial commitments.

00:09:58.470 --> 00:09:59.928 align:middle line:84%
It would be a real
stretch to think

00:09:59.928 --> 00:10:01.355 align:middle line:90%
about starting a second career.

00:10:01.355 --> 00:10:03.812 align:middle line:84%
>> Or it may require a
move in order to advance,

00:10:03.812 --> 00:10:04.770 align:middle line:90%
or something like that.

00:10:04.770 --> 00:10:06.620 align:middle line:84%
>> Or my family members
don't support this.

00:10:06.620 --> 00:10:09.650 align:middle line:84%
These could be obstacles
that are pieces of the puzzle

00:10:09.650 --> 00:10:11.783 align:middle line:84%
that you consciously
know about already.

00:10:11.783 --> 00:10:12.630 align:middle line:90%
>> OK.

00:10:12.630 --> 00:10:15.047 align:middle line:84%
>> But again, before you start
looking for the unconscious

00:10:15.047 --> 00:10:17.630 align:middle line:84%
to give you guidance or
synchronistic signs all around

00:10:17.630 --> 00:10:20.500 align:middle line:84%
you to point the way,
you do this homework.

00:10:20.500 --> 00:10:24.020 align:middle line:84%
Now, in step number five, with
a tentative decision already

00:10:24.020 --> 00:10:27.140 align:middle line:84%
sitting over here waiting,
you begin to open yourself

00:10:27.140 --> 00:10:28.100 align:middle line:90%
to your dreams.

00:10:28.100 --> 00:10:30.800 align:middle line:84%
You ask in meditation
for promptings,

00:10:30.800 --> 00:10:33.050 align:middle line:84%
you begin to watch for a
little synchronistic events,

00:10:33.050 --> 00:10:35.820 align:middle line:84%
like my license
plate, and so forth.

00:10:35.820 --> 00:10:37.550 align:middle line:84%
And you try to collect
as much as you can

00:10:37.550 --> 00:10:42.070 align:middle line:84%
from these more non-traditional
ways of getting input.

00:10:42.070 --> 00:10:45.350 align:middle line:84%
And I always say to people,
use more than one source.

00:10:45.350 --> 00:10:48.200 align:middle line:84%
And I even recommend working
with things like the "I

00:10:48.200 --> 00:10:51.620 align:middle line:84%
Ching" or astrology,
or tools that

00:10:51.620 --> 00:10:54.710 align:middle line:84%
can help us to
elicit or recognize

00:10:54.710 --> 00:10:56.790 align:middle line:90%
some of this guidance.

00:10:56.790 --> 00:10:59.330 align:middle line:84%
And then we've got to
evaluate the guidance,

00:10:59.330 --> 00:11:01.580 align:middle line:84%
and we don't want to become
superstitious about it.

00:11:01.580 --> 00:11:04.860 align:middle line:84%
We need to pick and choose
what resonates and feels right

00:11:04.860 --> 00:11:05.660 align:middle line:90%
to us.

00:11:05.660 --> 00:11:10.700 align:middle line:84%
>> When it feels right to
you, what is the experience?

00:11:10.700 --> 00:11:14.870 align:middle line:84%
>> It feels to me as if my
best self is being called

00:11:14.870 --> 00:11:16.640 align:middle line:90%
to the surface.

00:11:16.640 --> 00:11:18.290 align:middle line:84%
It feels as if
something within me

00:11:18.290 --> 00:11:20.120 align:middle line:84%
that knows what I
really ought to be doing

00:11:20.120 --> 00:11:23.120 align:middle line:84%
is being reminded
of that knowledge.

00:11:23.120 --> 00:11:26.960 align:middle line:84%
>> Isn't there a fraction,
too, the time that there is no

00:11:26.960 --> 00:11:29.100 align:middle line:90%
self-doubt in that moment?

00:11:29.100 --> 00:11:30.980 align:middle line:10%
Maybe the doubts
may come up later,

00:11:30.980 --> 00:11:33.190 align:middle line:10%
but in that moment
of pure knowing--

00:11:33.190 --> 00:11:35.870 align:middle line:10%
>> Oh, invariably,
the doubts creep in.

00:11:35.870 --> 00:11:38.000 align:middle line:84%
And even at step
number seven, where

00:11:38.000 --> 00:11:40.940 align:middle line:84%
you now have formulated
a guided decision

00:11:40.940 --> 00:11:43.370 align:middle line:84%
and you measure that against
your ideal, your core value

00:11:43.370 --> 00:11:44.995 align:middle line:84%
to make sure it's
pointing you in a way

00:11:44.995 --> 00:11:48.640 align:middle line:84%
that you can live with in
keeping with your best self,

00:11:48.640 --> 00:11:50.630 align:middle line:84%
there's still obstacles
that creep in,

00:11:50.630 --> 00:11:52.310 align:middle line:90%
there's doubts that creep in.

00:11:52.310 --> 00:11:53.810 align:middle line:84%
And then step eight
is to act on it.

00:11:53.810 --> 00:11:55.185 align:middle line:84%
But even as you're
acting, you've

00:11:55.185 --> 00:11:58.010 align:middle line:84%
got to deal with some of these
obstacles you're referring to.

00:11:58.010 --> 00:12:00.050 align:middle line:10%
>> I'd love for
you to go through--

00:12:00.050 --> 00:12:03.775 align:middle line:10%
in our next segment, to
go through a good example

00:12:03.775 --> 00:12:05.150 align:middle line:10%
or an example we
could relate to,

00:12:05.150 --> 00:12:07.790 align:middle line:10%
maybe it's the changing
jobs or whatever,

00:12:07.790 --> 00:12:11.210 align:middle line:10%
and give us an idea of how
we can go through each step.

00:12:11.210 --> 00:12:13.850 align:middle line:84%
And as I'm understanding,
too, it doesn't necessarily

00:12:13.850 --> 00:12:15.650 align:middle line:90%
happen in a day or two days.

00:12:15.650 --> 00:12:16.520 align:middle line:90%
That you may go--

00:12:16.520 --> 00:12:18.800 align:middle line:84%
I know I've done the
40-day journal before.

00:12:18.800 --> 00:12:20.510 align:middle line:84%
You may go a period
of time where

00:12:20.510 --> 00:12:22.863 align:middle line:84%
you're working on a
particular question

00:12:22.863 --> 00:12:24.530 align:middle line:84%
and looking for the
synchronistic events

00:12:24.530 --> 00:12:25.280 align:middle line:90%
at the same time.

00:12:25.280 --> 00:12:25.640 align:middle line:90%
>> OK.

00:12:25.640 --> 00:12:26.515 align:middle line:90%
I'll have an example.

00:12:26.515 --> 00:12:27.350 align:middle line:90%
>> OK.

00:12:27.350 --> 00:12:28.200 align:middle line:90%
Stay tuned.

