00:12:49.970 --> 00:12:53.105 align:middle line:10%
Now, Mark has written the book,
"Synchronicity as Spiritual

00:12:53.105 --> 00:12:54.980 align:middle line:10%
Guidance," and I think
one of the things that

00:12:54.980 --> 00:12:56.690 align:middle line:10%
came to mind
earlier was, what do

00:12:56.690 --> 00:13:00.590 align:middle line:10%
you say to people who
receive spiritual guidance

00:13:00.590 --> 00:13:04.350 align:middle line:10%
or awareness of synchronistic
events from other people?

00:13:04.350 --> 00:13:07.440 align:middle line:84%
Is this something that only
we can know the synchronicity

00:13:07.440 --> 00:13:08.240 align:middle line:90%
in our own life?

00:13:08.240 --> 00:13:10.550 align:middle line:84%
We can't know it for
someone else, can we?

00:13:10.550 --> 00:13:13.520 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, I think sometimes
we get messages that are

00:13:13.520 --> 00:13:14.660 align:middle line:90%
for our own self--

00:13:14.660 --> 00:13:18.470 align:middle line:84%
>> What do we do with that,
and how do we know it has some

00:13:18.470 --> 00:13:19.970 align:middle line:90%
value?

00:13:19.970 --> 00:13:21.650 align:middle line:84%
>> When you're on
a path yourself,

00:13:21.650 --> 00:13:24.500 align:middle line:84%
when you're working on
your own spirituality,

00:13:24.500 --> 00:13:27.440 align:middle line:84%
I think that you are open and
receptive to others sometimes

00:13:27.440 --> 00:13:29.820 align:middle line:84%
having a piece of
the puzzle for you.

00:13:29.820 --> 00:13:31.850 align:middle line:84%
And oftentimes, we
know because it fits.

00:13:31.850 --> 00:13:33.770 align:middle line:84%
You ever put together
a jigsaw puzzle

00:13:33.770 --> 00:13:35.750 align:middle line:84%
and you find one
that fits because

00:13:35.750 --> 00:13:39.348 align:middle line:84%
of the context of the other
pieces arranged around it?

00:13:39.348 --> 00:13:41.390 align:middle line:84%
In a similar way, when
you're working on yourself

00:13:41.390 --> 00:13:42.950 align:middle line:84%
and you're getting some
of your own pieces,

00:13:42.950 --> 00:13:44.990 align:middle line:84%
then when somebody else
has a piece to offer you

00:13:44.990 --> 00:13:48.080 align:middle line:84%
and it fits, then it's with a
greater sense of reliability

00:13:48.080 --> 00:13:50.810 align:middle line:84%
you can say, boy, thank you,
that was really of help to me

00:13:50.810 --> 00:13:51.230 align:middle line:90%
today.

00:13:51.230 --> 00:13:52.760 align:middle line:84%
>> It would be
important, I imagine,

00:13:52.760 --> 00:13:55.400 align:middle line:84%
to understand our own
intent in sharing that,

00:13:55.400 --> 00:13:58.250 align:middle line:84%
as well as perhaps the intent
of someone else and sharing

00:13:58.250 --> 00:14:01.880 align:middle line:84%
the information to
really know if it fits.

00:14:01.880 --> 00:14:04.640 align:middle line:10%
>> As skillful as I think Edgar
Cayce was for more than 40

00:14:04.640 --> 00:14:06.770 align:middle line:10%
years in giving spiritual
advice to others,

00:14:06.770 --> 00:14:09.440 align:middle line:10%
it's not surprising
people sometimes ask him,

00:14:09.440 --> 00:14:12.410 align:middle line:10%
what should I do if I think I'm
getting guidance for someone

00:14:12.410 --> 00:14:13.620 align:middle line:10%
else?

00:14:13.620 --> 00:14:16.170 align:middle line:84%
And his answer was, if you
feel like you've gotten a dream

00:14:16.170 --> 00:14:17.878 align:middle line:84%
and it's really
about somebody else,

00:14:17.878 --> 00:14:20.170 align:middle line:84%
or if you feel like you're
getting a meditation insight

00:14:20.170 --> 00:14:22.040 align:middle line:84%
and it's really
for someone else,

00:14:22.040 --> 00:14:24.320 align:middle line:84%
you should be willing to
share the information,

00:14:24.320 --> 00:14:26.512 align:middle line:90%
but never press the issue.

00:14:26.512 --> 00:14:28.220 align:middle line:84%
So if I've had a dream
and I think, maybe

00:14:28.220 --> 00:14:31.380 align:middle line:84%
it's really about Carolyn,
be willing to share it,

00:14:31.380 --> 00:14:33.780 align:middle line:84%
but do it in a way that
leaves it open for you to say,

00:14:33.780 --> 00:14:36.290 align:middle line:84%
well, I'm sure
that's not about me.

00:14:36.290 --> 00:14:38.450 align:middle line:84%
Or if I say I've had a
meditation experience where

00:14:38.450 --> 00:14:40.913 align:middle line:84%
I heard a little voice that
said something for you,

00:14:40.913 --> 00:14:42.830 align:middle line:84%
I would share it in a
way that left you plenty

00:14:42.830 --> 00:14:44.690 align:middle line:84%
of outs to say, well,
that's not for me,

00:14:44.690 --> 00:14:46.370 align:middle line:90%
that must be your own message.

00:14:46.370 --> 00:14:47.450 align:middle line:90%
To never press it.

00:14:47.450 --> 00:14:50.420 align:middle line:84%
>> I would think in my own
life, I think that if I do get

00:14:50.420 --> 00:14:53.870 align:middle line:84%
something, that I'm really
aware of how this might impact

00:14:53.870 --> 00:14:56.870 align:middle line:84%
the other person as well, and
to share it from a harmless

00:14:56.870 --> 00:14:58.100 align:middle line:90%
intent.

00:14:58.100 --> 00:15:01.460 align:middle line:84%
But if it doesn't feel
like that, to not share it.

00:15:01.460 --> 00:15:04.520 align:middle line:84%
You said you had an example
that will help us understand

00:15:04.520 --> 00:15:06.530 align:middle line:84%
the eight steps
that you delineate

00:15:06.530 --> 00:15:09.710 align:middle line:90%
in your book on synchronicity.

00:15:09.710 --> 00:15:10.580 align:middle line:90%
Give us an idea--

00:15:10.580 --> 00:15:11.840 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, I'm going to
tell a story on myself.

00:15:11.840 --> 00:15:12.350 align:middle line:90%
>> OK.

00:15:12.350 --> 00:15:14.350 align:middle line:84%
>> This goes back more
than a couple of decades,

00:15:14.350 --> 00:15:16.670 align:middle line:84%
when I was just getting
out of undergraduate school

00:15:16.670 --> 00:15:19.580 align:middle line:84%
in the last couple of weeks
of my senior year of college,

00:15:19.580 --> 00:15:21.770 align:middle line:84%
and I realized I faced
a very big decision.

00:15:21.770 --> 00:15:23.643 align:middle line:90%
What was I going to do next?

00:15:23.643 --> 00:15:25.310 align:middle line:84%
And so I went through
those eight steps,

00:15:25.310 --> 00:15:27.102 align:middle line:84%
which really come out
of the Cayce material

00:15:27.102 --> 00:15:28.970 align:middle line:84%
that I'd been studying
already in college.

00:15:28.970 --> 00:15:32.405 align:middle line:84%
And my spiritual ideal at
that time was loving service.

00:15:32.405 --> 00:15:34.280 align:middle line:84%
So I wanted to do
something with my life that

00:15:34.280 --> 00:15:36.860 align:middle line:90%
would bespeak loving service.

00:15:36.860 --> 00:15:38.030 align:middle line:90%
I wrote my question out.

00:15:38.030 --> 00:15:40.550 align:middle line:84%
What should I do
next upon graduation?

00:15:40.550 --> 00:15:42.160 align:middle line:90%
That's step two.

00:15:42.160 --> 00:15:44.570 align:middle line:84%
Step three was to collect
all the information

00:15:44.570 --> 00:15:47.720 align:middle line:84%
that I could just at a
commonsense, rational level.

00:15:47.720 --> 00:15:49.130 align:middle line:90%
And I began to look for options.

00:15:49.130 --> 00:15:51.530 align:middle line:84%
One was to go to
graduate school.

00:15:51.530 --> 00:15:54.560 align:middle line:84%
Another was to take a year off
and travel around the country,

00:15:54.560 --> 00:15:57.530 align:middle line:84%
and try to find myself,
as people back in that era

00:15:57.530 --> 00:15:58.910 align:middle line:90%
used to call it.

00:15:58.910 --> 00:16:02.750 align:middle line:84%
And a third was to go get a
job right away, heaven forbid.

00:16:02.750 --> 00:16:04.490 align:middle line:84%
But I saw at least
those three options,

00:16:04.490 --> 00:16:06.872 align:middle line:84%
and I was looking
into each one of them.

00:16:06.872 --> 00:16:08.330 align:middle line:84%
And the only place
that I can think

00:16:08.330 --> 00:16:10.760 align:middle line:84%
of where I might be
interested in getting a job

00:16:10.760 --> 00:16:12.530 align:middle line:84%
was to move to Virginia
Beach, Virginia

00:16:12.530 --> 00:16:15.215 align:middle line:84%
and try to work at the
Edgar Cayce Center.

00:16:15.215 --> 00:16:17.090 align:middle line:84%
But I was also considering
a graduate school,

00:16:17.090 --> 00:16:19.270 align:middle line:84%
and also this traveling
around a year.

00:16:19.270 --> 00:16:21.620 align:middle line:84%
And I finally made
a conscious decision

00:16:21.620 --> 00:16:23.330 align:middle line:84%
that I would move
to Virginia Beach,

00:16:23.330 --> 00:16:25.550 align:middle line:84%
and see if I could
get a job there.

00:16:25.550 --> 00:16:27.470 align:middle line:84%
Then I began to look
for guidance about

00:16:27.470 --> 00:16:29.780 align:middle line:84%
whether that would be an
appropriate decision or not.

00:16:29.780 --> 00:16:33.230 align:middle line:84%
>> Were you aware of all these
steps that you were doing

00:16:33.230 --> 00:16:34.150 align:middle line:90%
during the time?

00:16:34.150 --> 00:16:34.510 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, yes.

00:16:34.510 --> 00:16:36.050 align:middle line:84%
>> At that time, you
were aware of exact--

00:16:36.050 --> 00:16:37.800 align:middle line:84%
>> I knew about this
eight step procedure,

00:16:37.800 --> 00:16:40.600 align:middle line:84%
and I was doing it very
intentionally and consciously.

00:16:40.600 --> 00:16:43.490 align:middle line:84%
And I began to ask at the
end of every meditation time

00:16:43.490 --> 00:16:45.170 align:middle line:90%
for a prompting or an intuition.

00:16:45.170 --> 00:16:47.930 align:middle line:84%
I began to watch my
dreams very carefully.

00:16:47.930 --> 00:16:50.570 align:middle line:84%
I began to watch for little
signs of things that happened

00:16:50.570 --> 00:16:52.240 align:middle line:90%
and things people said to me.

00:16:52.240 --> 00:16:56.020 align:middle line:84%
Now, the most dramatic guidance
was a dream that I had,

00:16:56.020 --> 00:16:59.210 align:middle line:84%
and I dreamed just a couple
of weeks into this process

00:16:59.210 --> 00:17:01.520 align:middle line:84%
that I was sitting at a
table, just as you and I

00:17:01.520 --> 00:17:04.069 align:middle line:84%
are sitting here, and
across the table from me

00:17:04.069 --> 00:17:07.369 align:middle line:84%
was Edgar Cayce's grandson,
Charles Thomas Cayce.

00:17:07.369 --> 00:17:08.930 align:middle line:84%
And I had met him
at some conferences

00:17:08.930 --> 00:17:10.880 align:middle line:90%
when I was a college student.

00:17:10.880 --> 00:17:12.530 align:middle line:84%
He was working there
in Virginia Beach,

00:17:12.530 --> 00:17:14.030 align:middle line:84%
and he told me in
this dream that he

00:17:14.030 --> 00:17:16.670 align:middle line:84%
was getting ready to hire
somebody to work with him.

00:17:16.670 --> 00:17:19.930 align:middle line:84%
And in the dream I said, I'm
available, hire me, hire me.

00:17:19.930 --> 00:17:22.430 align:middle line:84%
And we talked and we talked,
and the last thing I remembered

00:17:22.430 --> 00:17:24.140 align:middle line:84%
him saying when I
woke up from the dream

00:17:24.140 --> 00:17:28.310 align:middle line:84%
was he had somebody else in
mind, and I could forget it,

00:17:28.310 --> 00:17:30.160 align:middle line:90%
there was no job for me there.

00:17:30.160 --> 00:17:32.730 align:middle line:84%
And I woke up from that dream,
and I was very discouraged,

00:17:32.730 --> 00:17:35.600 align:middle line:84%
but I remarked to myself
how this process works,

00:17:35.600 --> 00:17:37.453 align:middle line:90%
and I wrote the dream down.

00:17:37.453 --> 00:17:38.870 align:middle line:84%
And because of
that dream, I began

00:17:38.870 --> 00:17:41.550 align:middle line:84%
to set in motion one
of the other options.

00:17:41.550 --> 00:17:45.590 align:middle line:84%
Now, eight nights later,
I had a second dream.

00:17:45.590 --> 00:17:48.110 align:middle line:84%
I was walking down a
sidewalk in the second dream,

00:17:48.110 --> 00:17:51.380 align:middle line:84%
and here came this same
man, Charles Thomas Cayce.

00:17:51.380 --> 00:17:54.990 align:middle line:84%
He's still 100 feet away or so
when I hollered to him, hey,

00:17:54.990 --> 00:17:57.260 align:middle line:84%
I had a dream about
you the other night.

00:17:57.260 --> 00:17:59.990 align:middle line:84%
And as he's approaching
me, he hollers back,

00:17:59.990 --> 00:18:02.030 align:middle line:90%
I remember that dream.

00:18:02.030 --> 00:18:04.640 align:middle line:84%
And we're beginning to approach
each other, and he says,

00:18:04.640 --> 00:18:07.783 align:middle line:84%
but you forgot the
second half of the dream.

00:18:07.783 --> 00:18:09.200 align:middle line:84%
Mind you, I'm still
in this dream.

00:18:09.200 --> 00:18:10.840 align:middle line:90%
I don't know that I'm dreaming.

00:18:10.840 --> 00:18:13.310 align:middle line:84%
And I said, what
part did I forget?

00:18:13.310 --> 00:18:15.920 align:middle line:84%
And he said, when I told you
you couldn't have the job,

00:18:15.920 --> 00:18:18.320 align:middle line:84%
you didn't like my answer,
and you went and got

00:18:18.320 --> 00:18:21.290 align:middle line:84%
a file of everything you had
been doing for the last five

00:18:21.290 --> 00:18:22.340 align:middle line:90%
years.

00:18:22.340 --> 00:18:24.530 align:middle line:84%
And I looked through that
and I liked it so much,

00:18:24.530 --> 00:18:28.290 align:middle line:84%
I changed my mind and I told
you you could have the job.

00:18:28.290 --> 00:18:30.840 align:middle line:84%
And I said, that's
great, what is the job?

00:18:30.840 --> 00:18:33.890 align:middle line:84%
And he said, in charge of
college age young people

00:18:33.890 --> 00:18:36.110 align:middle line:90%
looking for God.

00:18:36.110 --> 00:18:37.910 align:middle line:84%
And then I said,
when does it start?

00:18:37.910 --> 00:18:41.010 align:middle line:84%
And he said, Christmas
day this year.

00:18:41.010 --> 00:18:43.760 align:middle line:84%
Now, mind you, this
dream was in May of 1972,

00:18:43.760 --> 00:18:46.580 align:middle line:84%
it's predicting months and
months into the future.

00:18:46.580 --> 00:18:48.890 align:middle line:84%
I woke up from the second
dream, wrote that down.

00:18:48.890 --> 00:18:50.670 align:middle line:90%
I was very excited.

00:18:50.670 --> 00:18:53.810 align:middle line:84%
I had other forms of guidance
as well that I evaluated.

00:18:53.810 --> 00:18:57.110 align:middle line:84%
But eventually, I made what
I felt was a guided decision,

00:18:57.110 --> 00:19:01.700 align:middle line:84%
took a risk, moved 1,000 miles
to Virginia Beach, got there.

00:19:01.700 --> 00:19:04.010 align:middle line:84%
And as you pointed out,
sometimes there's obstacles.

00:19:04.010 --> 00:19:06.260 align:middle line:90%
There was no job.

00:19:06.260 --> 00:19:09.140 align:middle line:84%
That was all I could do to
keep from going up to see him

00:19:09.140 --> 00:19:10.730 align:middle line:84%
in the waking flesh
and blood state

00:19:10.730 --> 00:19:12.355 align:middle line:84%
and telling him the
dreams, and saying,

00:19:12.355 --> 00:19:13.700 align:middle line:90%
where's the job you promised?

00:19:13.700 --> 00:19:14.500 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:19:14.500 --> 00:19:15.670 align:middle line:90%
>> But I didn't do that.

00:19:15.670 --> 00:19:18.500 align:middle line:84%
And I hung around for a while
and found some little odds

00:19:18.500 --> 00:19:19.970 align:middle line:90%
and ends jobs.

00:19:19.970 --> 00:19:22.280 align:middle line:84%
And then somebody
announced he was going off

00:19:22.280 --> 00:19:25.330 align:middle line:84%
to graduate school, and
I applied for that job

00:19:25.330 --> 00:19:26.130 align:middle line:90%
and I got it.

00:19:26.130 --> 00:19:28.550 align:middle line:84%
And it was youth
activities coordinator,

00:19:28.550 --> 00:19:31.590 align:middle line:84%
and it began New
Year's Day 1973.

00:19:31.590 --> 00:19:35.270 align:middle line:84%
It was within seven days of
what that dream had predicted.

00:19:35.270 --> 00:19:37.430 align:middle line:84%
>> Where was the
spiritual guidance?

00:19:37.430 --> 00:19:39.420 align:middle line:90%
Where was the synchronicity?

00:19:39.420 --> 00:19:43.770 align:middle line:84%
I know in various places,
but how would you say--

00:19:43.770 --> 00:19:45.770 align:middle line:84%
what is the difference
between the synchronicity

00:19:45.770 --> 00:19:47.030 align:middle line:90%
and the spiritual guidance?

00:19:47.030 --> 00:19:50.330 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, synchronicity,
as Carl Jung describes it,

00:19:50.330 --> 00:19:53.360 align:middle line:84%
is a law of the universe that
just describes the way in which

00:19:53.360 --> 00:19:55.700 align:middle line:84%
things are meaningfully
connected to each other that

00:19:55.700 --> 00:20:00.220 align:middle line:84%
couldn't be explained by
physical cause and effect.

00:20:00.220 --> 00:20:02.990 align:middle line:84%
And Jung always pointed
out that these outer signs

00:20:02.990 --> 00:20:05.000 align:middle line:84%
need to correspond
to inner signs

00:20:05.000 --> 00:20:07.880 align:middle line:84%
as well, if it's
truly synchronistic.

00:20:07.880 --> 00:20:11.510 align:middle line:84%
Just the coincidence of noticing
that the baseball score today

00:20:11.510 --> 00:20:14.390 align:middle line:84%
was 7 to 3, and
then you get home

00:20:14.390 --> 00:20:17.330 align:middle line:84%
and you receive something
in the mail that

00:20:17.330 --> 00:20:20.090 align:middle line:84%
says you're lucky
number is 73, and then

00:20:20.090 --> 00:20:23.120 align:middle line:84%
you are watching channel
73 on television tonight

00:20:23.120 --> 00:20:24.835 align:middle line:84%
and something
interesting happens,

00:20:24.835 --> 00:20:26.210 align:middle line:84%
it's hard to know
how any of that

00:20:26.210 --> 00:20:28.640 align:middle line:84%
corresponds to an
inner soul event.

00:20:28.640 --> 00:20:31.370 align:middle line:84%
So in the deepest sense,
that's not synchronistic.

00:20:31.370 --> 00:20:33.770 align:middle line:84%
But as I was wrestling with
this deep question of what

00:20:33.770 --> 00:20:37.550 align:middle line:84%
am I going to do with my life,
and as I'm having dreams,

00:20:37.550 --> 00:20:40.753 align:middle line:84%
or in this case, a series of
dreams that's pointing the way,

00:20:40.753 --> 00:20:42.170 align:middle line:84%
and as there were
other signs that

00:20:42.170 --> 00:20:43.910 align:middle line:84%
had to do with
things people said

00:20:43.910 --> 00:20:46.397 align:middle line:84%
or somebody moving to
Virginia Beach right before me

00:20:46.397 --> 00:20:48.230 align:middle line:84%
and saying if you ever
need a place to stay,

00:20:48.230 --> 00:20:51.260 align:middle line:84%
even for a month at a time,
my house is open to you,

00:20:51.260 --> 00:20:54.710 align:middle line:84%
those other little things
that fell into place to me

00:20:54.710 --> 00:20:57.080 align:middle line:84%
were suggestive of this
being the right path for me.

00:20:57.080 --> 00:21:00.470 align:middle line:84%
>> So we're following
synchronistic events also.

00:21:00.470 --> 00:21:03.740 align:middle line:84%
If we've got a question and
wanting to find the answer,

00:21:03.740 --> 00:21:06.230 align:middle line:84%
we pivot towards the
synchronistic events,

00:21:06.230 --> 00:21:08.512 align:middle line:84%
paying attention to them
to know our next step.

00:21:08.512 --> 00:21:10.970 align:middle line:84%
>> Or you can invite them, you
can make yourself more alert

00:21:10.970 --> 00:21:13.100 align:middle line:84%
for them by doing something
like the "I Ching,"

00:21:13.100 --> 00:21:17.330 align:middle line:84%
which is a 3,000 year old
Chinese Daoist divination

00:21:17.330 --> 00:21:19.580 align:middle line:84%
method, where you
can throw coins--

00:21:19.580 --> 00:21:21.620 align:middle line:84%
three coins six
consecutive times,

00:21:21.620 --> 00:21:24.320 align:middle line:84%
and you, by the way they
fall heads and tails,

00:21:24.320 --> 00:21:26.300 align:middle line:90%
build a hexagram.

00:21:26.300 --> 00:21:29.270 align:middle line:84%
And then you look in this book
of wisdom called the "I Ching,"

00:21:29.270 --> 00:21:32.600 align:middle line:84%
because there's 64 possible
ways in which those tosses can

00:21:32.600 --> 00:21:33.860 align:middle line:90%
turn out.

00:21:33.860 --> 00:21:36.020 align:middle line:84%
And in an uncanny,
synchronistic kind

00:21:36.020 --> 00:21:39.330 align:middle line:84%
of way, what you read in
the book for the hexagram

00:21:39.330 --> 00:21:41.690 align:middle line:84%
you've thrown is often
deeply related to the issue

00:21:41.690 --> 00:21:43.160 align:middle line:90%
that you're wrestling with.

00:21:43.160 --> 00:21:47.230 align:middle line:84%
>> I've often heard it
said that God doesn't work

00:21:47.230 --> 00:21:49.490 align:middle line:90%
in hypothetical situations.

00:21:49.490 --> 00:21:51.200 align:middle line:84%
But I'm wondering,
when you're getting

00:21:51.200 --> 00:21:52.670 align:middle line:84%
the synchronistic
events and you're

00:21:52.670 --> 00:21:55.040 align:middle line:84%
paying attention to
them, that they can also

00:21:55.040 --> 00:21:56.840 align:middle line:90%
direct you on the right path.

00:21:56.840 --> 00:22:00.050 align:middle line:84%
But could you also see
in synchronistic events

00:22:00.050 --> 00:22:02.990 align:middle line:84%
maybe the steps that
you do not need to take?

00:22:02.990 --> 00:22:05.540 align:middle line:84%
>> I think you can get
warnings, for sure.

00:22:05.540 --> 00:22:08.960 align:middle line:84%
I think you can get
indications that we can learn

00:22:08.960 --> 00:22:10.730 align:middle line:90%
from whichever path we take.

00:22:10.730 --> 00:22:12.542 align:middle line:84%
In a sense, there's
never a wrong decision,

00:22:12.542 --> 00:22:14.000 align:middle line:84%
but that there's
something that can

00:22:14.000 --> 00:22:15.208 align:middle line:90%
be learned from any decision.

00:22:15.208 --> 00:22:16.008 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:22:16.008 --> 00:22:18.230 align:middle line:84%
>> But there are some pathways
that are less painful,

00:22:18.230 --> 00:22:20.990 align:middle line:84%
more graceful, and they
really optimize our learning.

00:22:20.990 --> 00:22:23.900 align:middle line:84%
And I think as we become
alert for these signposts,

00:22:23.900 --> 00:22:27.080 align:middle line:84%
we're going to find the more
optimal way to chart our lives.

00:22:27.080 --> 00:22:29.660 align:middle line:84%
>> Dr. Mark Thurston, thank
you for being with us today.

00:22:29.660 --> 00:22:32.570 align:middle line:90%
Your book, among many others--

00:22:32.570 --> 00:22:33.900 align:middle line:90%
is it 16, the total now?

00:22:33.900 --> 00:22:34.700 align:middle line:90%
Or we have a--

00:22:34.700 --> 00:22:36.710 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:22:36.710 --> 00:22:39.402 align:middle line:84%
"Synchronicity as Spiritual
Guidance, All of Life

00:22:39.402 --> 00:22:41.360 align:middle line:84%
is Working Together to
Leave You Little Hints."

00:22:41.360 --> 00:22:43.950 align:middle line:84%
Thank you so much for
being with us today.

00:22:43.950 --> 00:22:46.640 align:middle line:84%
And thank you for joining
us on a world of wisdom.

00:22:46.640 --> 00:22:47.510 align:middle line:90%
I'm Carolyn Craft.

